ABOUT:

ASCIImui is a simple MUI program that converts a character into it's
corresponding ASCII code. It was compiled with gcc 2.95.3-4 and tested on
my machine (specs below).

I wrote ASCIImui in order to learn how to write MUI-based programs
with gcc. It's not that complicated, but it works!

ASCIImui is EMAILWARE (yes, that means you...).  If you find it or the
source code useful please send me an email!  I've also begun to write a
MUI/gcc tutorial that uses this source code as it's basis:

http://www.ezcyberspace.com/gcc

Enjoy! :-)
